It's not visible to the naked eye, but drinking water contains microplastics. We are potentially ingesting these microplastics every day though, according to the World Health Organisation (WHO), it is nothing to worry about yet. On Thursday, the organisation released its report on potential health risks with ingesting microplastics. There is limited data, but the data so far has been reassuring. 6 ways to avoid microplastics The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration says that microplastics are a major source of global pollution.